{
  "texts": [
    "They apply a PAC-Bayes bound similar to Theorem 2.7 and provide an explicit upper bound on log dρ dπ.",
    "This analysis gives a bound on R(θ T), that is, a bound on the risk of a deterministic predictor (up to the initialization).",
    "This is related to information bounds on similar algorithms that will be discussed in Subsection 6.6.2.",
    "We end this section by one more variant of the initial PAC-Bayes bound in Theorem 2.1: a bound in expectation with respect to the sample.",
    "Theorem 2.8."
  ]
}